# Workflow: Duplicate Stories â†’ Poems

## 1. Configure collections in _config.yml
Add poems alongside stories:
collections:
  stories:
    output: true
  poems:
    output: true

## 2. Create a landing page for poems
File: poems.md
---
layout: default
title: Poems
permalink: /poems/
---
<h2>Poems</h2>
<ul>
  {% for poem in site.poems %}
    <li><a href="{{ poem.url | relative_url }}">{{ poem.title }}</a></li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>

## 3. Create the poems collection folder
Directory: _poems/
Inside it, create Markdown files for each poem.

Example: _poems/first.md
---
layout: default
title: First Poem
---
This is the content of the first poem.

## 4. Update navigation in _layouts/default.html
Add a link to Poems alongside Stories:
<a href="{{ '/stories/' | relative_url }}">Stories</a> |
<a href="{{ '/poems/' | relative_url }}">Poems</a>

## 5. Build and verify
Run:
bundle exec jekyll serve
Check:
- /stories/ shows stories menu
- /poems/ shows poems menu
- Individual poems render with site CSS

